projectsArray.title: Vue Portfolio Website
projectsArray.about: This project has taken a great amount of energy, focus, and education to create a website that I feel is representative of me and the kind of work you can expect from me. I started this in late-Septemer of 2022 and it is an ongoing project.

projectsArray.title: The Dog API
projectsArray.about: This project takes advantage of axios, express.js, and other libraries to make Api calls to the dog-api, parsing the data returned to render the data

projectsArray.title: Frontera Devs Main site
projectsArray.about: This project was done in collaboration with another officer of Fronter Devs. Built using React, we created this from scrathc, and we are now in the process of introducing scalability enhancements to make adding features easier

projectsArray.title: Frontera Hacks
projectsArray.about: This project was built upon the MLH boilerplate website template for hackathons, using Ruby and Jekyll. I had never used Ruby before starting on this project; however, I was able to easily understand the syntax and the implementation of the template's code to spearhead development.

projectsArray.title: Machine Intelligence Home Page
projectsArray.about: This site does not involve that much backend logic; however, the frontend was built using "vanilla" HTML/CSS/Javascript Stack. It is run using the UTRGV
